==============================================================================
1. COEFFICIENT REGISTER VALUES
==============================================================================

The gb_x570 fixup in patch_realtek.c writes these four coefficients.
Read back via hda-verb using SET_COEF_INDEX (0x500) + GET_PROC_COEF (0xc00)
on NID 0x20 (vendor-defined processing widget).

  COEF 0x07 = 0x3c0    (fixup writes 0x03c0)  MATCH
  COEF 0x1a = 0x1c1    (fixup writes 0x01c1)  MATCH
  COEF 0x1b = 0x202    (fixup writes 0x0202)  MATCH
  COEF 0x43 = 0x3005   (fixup writes 0x3005)  MATCH

All four coefficients match the gb_x570 fixup values exactly.
The fixup is active and has been applied to this boot session.

Commands used:
  sudo hda-verb /dev/snd/hwC3D0 0x20 0x500 <idx>   # SET_COEF_INDEX
  sudo hda-verb /dev/snd/hwC3D0 0x20 0xc00 0x0      # GET_PROC_COEF

NOTE: The plan's original script used verb 0xd00 (GET_COEF_INDEX) for the
data read, which returns the index register itself, not the coefficient
data. Corrected to 0xc00 (GET_PROC_COEF) for this probe.

