==============================================================================
9. ANALYSIS / NEXT STEPS
==============================================================================

Findings:
  - All four gb_x570 coef values are already applied (expected)
  - Node 0x1b has 5 hardware connections but fixup restricts to {0x0c}
  - Only 1 analog PCM exists; no second stream available
  - Four unused DACs (0x03, 0x04, 0x05, 0x25) available for routing
  - DAC 0x03 -> Mixer 0x0d is the natural target for 0x1b

Next: Phase 2b — Boot with model=generic to skip the fixup entirely.
This will let the generic parser see all 5 connections on 0x1b and
potentially auto-assign DAC 0x03 to it as an independent output.

Create /etc/modprobe.d/test-generic.conf:
  options snd-hda-codec-realtek model=generic

Then reboot and re-run probes to compare.
